			.chip.orange.lighten-5 grunt-contrib-concat

			p It is a good practice to concatenate and minify all javascript files into a single file for performance reasons. Same is true for CSS.
			
			p An HTML page may depend on multiple javascript files and css files. Each file is downloaded in the user's system using a separate HTTP call. Hence, if all the dependent javascript files are concatenated and minified to form a single file and if the same is also done for CSS, only two HTTP requests will be sufficient - one for javascript and one for CSS. This is expected to reduce the overall load time of the web page.
			
